headline: Can EMCOR Maintain Its 9.1% Margin Streak as Data Centers Explode?
summary: EME's improving margin streak is being tested as data center demand reshapes backlog, execution discipline and operating leverage.

headline: Has EMCOR’s 2025 Surge Gone Too Far or Do Cash Flows Suggest More Upside?
summary: Wondering if EMCOR Group is still good value after its huge run, or if the best days are already priced in, you are not alone. The stock has climbed 36.5% year to date and 329.7% over 3 years, while even the last month saw a steady 0.8% rise off a recent close around $624.56. Much of this strength has been underpinned by ongoing infrastructure spending, a solid backlog in mechanical and electrical projects, and steady contract wins in areas like data centers and mission critical facilities...
